# WhatsApp Messaging

Send and receive WhatsApp messages through the Twilio WhatsApp Business API. WhatsApp uses the same Messaging API as SMS (see [[twilio/sms]]) with `whatsapp:` prefixed phone numbers.

## Setup

To use WhatsApp in production, you need a registered WhatsApp Business Profile linked to your Twilio account. For development, use the Twilio Sandbox for WhatsApp — join by sending a code word to the sandbox number from your WhatsApp app.

1. Go to Twilio Console > Messaging > Try it out > Send a WhatsApp message
2. Send the join code from your WhatsApp to the sandbox number
3. Use the sandbox number as your `from` in API calls

## Sending a Message

```javascript
const twilio = require("twilio");

const client = twilio(
  process.env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID,
  process.env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN
);

const message = await client.messages.create({
  to: "whatsapp:+15551234567",
  from: "whatsapp:+14155238886", // Sandbox or registered number
  body: "Hello from Twilio WhatsApp!",
});

console.log(message.sid); // SM...
```

## Template Messages

WhatsApp requires pre-approved templates for messages sent outside the 24-hour session window (i.e., when you are initiating a conversation). Templates are registered through the WhatsApp Business Manager and approved by Meta.

```javascript
const message = await client.messages.create({
  to: "whatsapp:+15551234567",
  from: "whatsapp:+14155238886",
  body: "Your order #12345 has been shipped and will arrive by April 12.",
  // This matches an approved template pattern
});
```

Session messages (replies within 24 hours of the user's last message) can contain any content without template approval.

## Media Messages

Send images, documents, audio, and video via WhatsApp:

```javascript
const message = await client.messages.create({
  to: "whatsapp:+15551234567",
  from: "whatsapp:+14155238886",
  body: "Here is your receipt",
  mediaUrl: ["https://example.com/receipt.pdf"],
});
```

Supported media types: JPEG, PNG, PDF, MP3, MP4, OGG. Maximum file size is 16 MB for most types.

## Sandbox

The Twilio Sandbox allows testing without a production WhatsApp Business Profile. Sandbox limitations:

- Only pre-joined numbers can receive messages
- Limited to the sandbox phone number (`+14155238886`)
- Cannot use custom templates
- Intended for development only

For production, register a WhatsApp Business Profile through Twilio Console > Messaging > Senders > WhatsApp Senders.
